{"title_page": "Meena Singh (Manpur politician)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n'''Meena Singh''' is an Indian politician from [[Umaria district]] in [[Madhya Pradesh]]. She belongs to [[Bharatiya Janata Party|Bhartiya Janata Party]] and elected as MLA of [[Manpur, Indore|Manpur]] Town near Mhow [[Dr. Ambedkar Nagar|(Dr. Ambedkar Nagar)]]. She took Oath as a Minister of Tribal Welfare of [[Madhya Pradesh]] under CM [[Shivraj Singh Chouhan|Shivraj Singh Chauhan]]'s Cabinet formation on 21st April 2020.\n{{Infobox Indian politician\n| name        = Meena Singh\n| image       =\n| alt         =\n| caption     = \n| office1 = [[Government of Madhya Pradesh|Minister of Tribal Welfare<br/>Madhya Pradesh Government]]\n| term_start1 = 21 April 2020\n| term_end1 = \n| office3 = [[Madhya Pradesh Legislative Assembly|Member Of Legislative Assembly<br>Madhya Pradesh]]\n| constituency3 = [[Manpur (Vidhan Sabha constituency)|Manpur]]\n| term_start3 = 2008\n| term_end3 = \n| constituency4 = Nowrozabad\n| term_start4 = 2003\n| term_end4 = 2008\n| party = [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n| birth_name  = \n| birth_date  =\n| birth_place = \n| death_date  = \n| death_place =\n| nationality = Indian\n| other_names = \n| occupation  = \n| father      = \n| children    = \n| spouse      = \n| residence   = Belsara Village,Umaria District\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Singh, Meena, Manpur}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Umaria district]]\n[[Category:Madhya Pradesh MLAs 2008\u20132013]]\n[[Category:Women in Madhya Pradesh politics]]\n[[Category:Bharatiya Janata Party politicians from Madhya Pradesh]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian women politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Indian politicians]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{BJP-politician-stub}}\n{{MadhyaPradesh-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2019}}\n'''Meena Singh''' is an Indian politician from [[Umaria district]] in [